			"value":"<p class=\"flavour\"><i>By drawing attention to another, you can slip away.</i></p><p class=\"power-basics\"><b>Encounter</b></p><p class=\"power-basics\"><b>Minor Action</b><b> &#8226; </b>Personal</p><p class=\"power-basics\"><b>Requirement:</b> At least two creatures must be within 1 square of you and be able to see and hear you. </p><p><b>Effect:</b> Make a Bluff check to create a diversion to hide. If you succeed against one creature within 1 square of you, you succeed against all creatures within 1 square of you. In addition, if you use your skulking spy power on the same turn after using this power, that use of skulking spy allows you to shift through enemy spaces. </p><p>Published in Dragon Magazine 426. </p>",
